<br>
In all other fields where big multi-corporations have squashed the specialists companies of that field, there has been a degradation of quality once the specialist competitors are out of the field, and the multi-corporations are free to reign.<br>
<br>
Simply because you cannot focus as much on one ball, when you're juggling 5 of them.<br>
<br>
Nintendo is important because it doesn't allow Sony and Microsoft to slack off. It keeps them on edge. You have to be on edge when competing with a specialist.<br>
