<br>
Yes, the folks at the X-box team are focused and dedicated, they're gamers, and know their hats, but they are still subject to the main(?) corporation. When the main(?) corporation decides that games aren't in such high demand\competition, they have the power to cut funds or channel money.<br>
<br>
That's the way multi-corporations work.<br>
<br>
I, for one, value tradition. Nintendo is a part of the cultural history of games.<br>
Nintendo is about games. If they don't make games, there is no Nintendo. <br>
<br>
Sony(Not specifically the PS2 team) and Microsoft(Not specifically the X-Box team) is in a completely different ballgame. <br>
